{"id":58,"date":"2020-04-27T05:00:30","date_gmt":"2020-04-27T05:00:30","guid":{"rendered":"\/?page_id=58"},"modified":"2024-10-16T14:02:28","modified_gmt":"2024-10-16T14:02:28","slug":"tools","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/verifiedvoting.org\/tools\/","title":{"rendered":"Tools"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wpb-content-wrapper\"><p>[vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row&#8221; el_class=&#8221;title-banner who-we-are&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1588865020488{background-image: url(\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/who-we-are-header.png?id=172) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/4&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=&#8221;title&#8221; width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h1>Our Tools<\/h1>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Verified Voting\u2019s tools help explain how votes are cast and counted.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/4&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<a href=\"\/verifier\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-296 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/verifier.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1113\" height=\"516\" \/><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"red-text\">The Verifier<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Verifier is our interactive tool that lets you explore voting equipment usage and post-election audit requirements across the United States. It includes the most comprehensive publicly available data set on voting equipment going back to 2006, which is constantly being tracked and updated by our data team <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u2014 a surprisingly complex undertaking as choices about voting systems often happen at the county or township level. The map also shows post-election audit requirements by state from our <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/verifiedvoting.org\/auditlaws\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Audit Law Database<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The Verifier is a trusted resource for everyone \u2014 including government officials, independent researchers, journalists, and everyday voters\u00a0 \u2014 and has informed election protection efforts, election security legislation, and everything in between.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<a class=\"red-btn\" href=\"\/verifier\/\">MORE<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<a href=\"\/equipmentdb\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-297 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/voting-equipment-database.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1113\" height=\"516\" \/><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"red-text\">Voting Equipment Database<\/h3>\n<p>Verified Voting&#8217;s in-house database of voting equipment provides extensive background on the equipment used to cast &#8211; and count &#8211; votes. The U.S.&#8217;s aging voting equipment makes its election infrastructure vulnerable, and some states have more resilient voting equipment than others. Purchase (procurement) decisions about voting equipment may be made statewide or locally. Voting equipment undergoes certification by the U.S. Election Assistance Commission (EAC) and state election certification bodies.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<a class=\"red-btn\" href=\"\/equipmentdb\/\">MORE<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<a href=\"\/auditlaws\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-320 size-full\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/state-profiles.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"464\" \/><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"red-text\">Audit Law Database<\/h3>\n<p>The Verified Voting Audit Law Database is a resource that describes state laws, regulations, and procedures for post-election audits. This database was originally created and maintained by Citizens for Election Integrity Minnesota. The database migrated to Verified Voting in March 2017.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<a class=\"red-btn\" href=\"\/auditlaws\/\">MORE<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"\/recountlaws\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-320 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/verifiedvoting.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/recountstoolsimage.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"464\" \/><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"red-text\">Recount Law Database<\/h3>\n<p>The Verified Voting State Recount Law Databaseis a resource that describes state laws, regulations, and procedures for post-election recounts. This database was originally created and maintained by Citizens for Election Integrity Minnesota. The database migrated to Verified Voting in October 2024.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<a class=\"red-btn\" href=\"\/recountlaws\/\">MORE<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row&#8221; el_class=&#8221;support-banner&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text el_class=&#8221;banner-title&#8221;]<\/p>\n<div class=\"title-label\">Support<\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"red-text\">Secure<\/span> <span class=\"blue-text\">Elections<\/span><\/h3>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=&#8221;30&#8243;][vc_column_inner el_class=&#8221;right-border&#8221; width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h4 class=\"red-text\">Donate to Verified Voting<\/h4>\n<p>A strong and healthy democracy depends on the security of our elections. Join us and help ensure that every vote counts.<\/p>\n<p><a class=\"donate-link\" href=\"\/donate\/\">Donate<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h4 class=\"blue-text\">Join Our Mailing List<\/h4>\n<p>The election landscape is constantly changing and full of complexities. We\u2019ll keep you informed on what\u2019s happening, and what we\u2019re doing to make elections accurate and secure.<\/p>\n<div class=\"wpcf7 no-js\" id=\"wpcf7-f180-o1\" lang=\"en-US\" dir=\"ltr\" data-wpcf7-id=\"180\">\n<div class=\"screen-reader-response\"><p role=\"status\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"true\"><\/p> <ul><\/ul><\/div>\n<form action=\"\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/58#wpcf7-f180-o1\" method=\"post\" class=\"wpcf7-form init mailchimp-ext-0.5.72\" aria-label=\"Contact form\" novalidate=\"novalidate\" data-status=\"init\">\n<div style=\"display: none;\">\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7\" value=\"180\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_version\" value=\"6.0\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_locale\" value=\"en_US\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_unit_tag\" value=\"wpcf7-f180-o1\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_container_post\" value=\"0\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_posted_data_hash\" value=\"\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_recaptcha_response\" value=\"\" \/>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"subscribe-form-wrapper\">\n\t<p><label><span class=\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap\" data-name=\"your-email\"><input size=\"40\" maxlength=\"400\" class=\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-email wpcf7-validates-as-required wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-email\" aria-required=\"true\" aria-invalid=\"false\" value=\"\" type=\"email\" name=\"your-email\" \/><\/span> <\/label><input class=\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-submit has-spinner\" type=\"submit\" value=\"SIGN UP\" \/>\n\t<\/p>\n<\/div><p style=\"display: none !important;\" class=\"akismet-fields-container\" data-prefix=\"_wpcf7_ak_\"><label>&#916;<textarea name=\"_wpcf7_ak_hp_textarea\" cols=\"45\" rows=\"8\" maxlength=\"100\"><\/textarea><\/